The paper deals with distributed consensus protocols and anonymous communication, which are topics typically covered in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of timing attacks and the focus on reliable broadcast also suggest Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as possible sub-categories.
